</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-28_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-29_ pf-text-1">According to the Health and Safety Executive (HSE), in 2019/20, there were approximately 693,000 non-fatal injuries at work in Great Britain. Of these, around 111,000 injuries required more than seven days of absence from work.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-31_ pf-text-1">Proper recording of accidents, including first aid incidents, is essential for accurately assessing risks, identifying trends, and implementing preventive measures.







</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-33_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-34_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-35_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-37_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-38_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid incident </strong>- Any sudden injury or illness that requires immediate medical attention and is typically addressed by trained first aiders or designated personnel.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-40_ pf-text-1"><strong>Accident recording</strong> - The systematic documentation of workplace incidents, including details such as date, time, location, nature of the incident, and actions taken.








</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-42_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fatbYi lnCFtg pf-43_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cXPBhi kkWDYP pf-44_ pf-heading-1-h3">Relevant legislation and regulations</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-btwLGw cuLvxI pf-46_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-47_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974 (HSWA) places a legal duty on employers to ensure the health, safety, and welfare of their employees.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-49_ pf-text-1">The Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999 require employers to assess and manage risks, including the provision of adequate first aid facilities and arrangements.







</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-gFmZvT eCWkjm pf-51_ pf-text-1">The Reporting of Injuries, Diseases and Dangerous Occurrences Regulations 2013 (RIDDOR) mandates the reporting of certain workplace incidents, including those resulting in specified injuries or fatalities.







</li></ul><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Compliance with relevant legislation, such as the HSWA and RIDDOR, is paramount for employers. Failure to comply with these regulations not only puts employees at risk but can also result in legal consequences and reputational damage for the organisation.<em></em>
<br>
